{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make home sellers liable for costs incurred by buyers if they pull out",
        "additional_details": "If the Seller pulls out before the exchange of contract, they should be liable for the these costs such as valuations and surveys which cost \u00a3100 or more and any other cost spent by the buyer thinking the sale will go ahead.\r\n\r\nIf 10 sellers pull out of the sale before contract exchange,  a single buyer could potentially lose thousands on valuations, solicitors' and mortgage advisers fees etc.  The buyer's bank lending the mortgage will also conduct a hard search against the buyer's credit file which can contribute to a lower credit score.  It's not fair.",
        "background": "Buyers can spend hundreds of pounds thinking the property sale will go ahead. ",
